mic analyses, and poetic works, Kānepu'u and Poepoe created a record of Hawaiian cultural history and thought in order to transmit ancestral knowledge to future generations. Celebrating indigenous intellectual agency in the midst of US imperialism, The Power of the Steel-tipped Pen is a call for the further restoration of native Hawaiian intellectual history to help ground contemporary Hawaiian thought, culture, and governance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aHawaii - History - 19th century - Sources. 0aHawaiian languagexSocial aspects. 0aHawaiian literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHawaiian newspapersxHistoryy19th century. 0aHawaiian philosophy. 0aHawaiiansvSongs and music. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh1 aThiong'o, Ngugi Wa08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822373131zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822373131423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822373131.jpg  a978-3-11-069634-9  DUK eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles